<SectionWrapper>
    <SectionLeft>
        <h2>RTL Support</h2>
        <p style=" margin-top: 1em;">
            Foundation support right-to-left css for hebrew or other cultures reading from right to left.
        </p>
        <p style=" margin-top: 1em;">
            To activate rtl feature, use <Code>bf_rtl.css</Code> and replace html tag to <Code Content="PGh0bWwgY2xhc3M9Im5vLWpzIiBsYW5nPSJoZSIgZGlyPSJydGwiPg==" />.
        </p>
        <h3>Language Code</h3>
        <p>You'll need to change your lang attribute value to match your language. Here's a handy list of common right-to-left languages and their html codes.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Hebrew: he, iw</li>
            <li>Yiddish: yi, ji</li>
            <li>Arabic: ar</li>
            <li>Farsi: fa</li>            
            <li>Urdu: ur</li>
        </ul>
        <NavLink href="https://www.loc.gov/standards/iso639-2/php/code_list.php">See more Languages</NavLink>
        <hr />
    </SectionLeft>
</SectionWrapper>


